      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "@sipa I can't convince myself that returning `T&&` wouldn't mess up lifetimes somehow and return a dangling reference... Trying it out, it seems like `T` as the return-type might invoke the move constructor while `T&&` might not, so what you say at least seems plausible. I think the current approach (with a lambda) also invokes the move constructor; though destruction happens in a different order...",
