      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "@sipa I think my concern is that `f(1+2) + 4` might be interpreted as \"pass 3 to f, then destruct 3, then add 4 to whatever  f returned\" which would cause a problem if f were returning the 3 object that was just destructed. But I think \"[All temporary objects are destroyed as the last step in evaluating the full-expression that (lexically) contains the point where they were created,](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/lifetime)\" means that's not allowed?",
